- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the societal impact and implications of MOOC and crowdsourcing phenomena. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the IT mediation and techniques designed to attract and maintain participant activity in both domains. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper mentions knowledge generating capabilities in both domains. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is another possible category as the paper discusses the presence of intermediary service providers in both domains. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the varying levels of openness to participants in both domains.
